# Page Objects and Fixtures

## Page objects

- Extend `BasePage`; define `url` at the top; use `constructor(page)` and call `super(page, url)`.
- Expose elements via getters (no args) or methods (with args), e.g. `get heading` vs `listButton(text)`.
- When creating Elements (Button, TextArea, BaseElement), always pass a single options object, not positional args.

```javascript
// BAD
return new TextArea(this.page, "#couponCode1");

// GOOD
return new TextArea({ page: this.page, selector: "#couponCode1" });
return new Button({ page: this.page, text: "Save" });
```

## Fixtures

- Use `test.extend({ ... })` from `@playwright/test`; create the page object from `page`, then call `use(fixture)` in the fixture function.
- Fixture names are camelCase (e.g. `homePage`).
